The files:

* baddx.run
* badspotter.run
* badnode.run
* badword.new.run

contain the DXSpider commands required to insert the entries they include.

They have been provided in this “.run” format so the original files are not overwritten.

You can view them from a Linux shell with a simple command such as:
`cat <file.run>`

Then copy/paste the output directly into the DXSpider console.

If an entry already exists, it will not be overwritten.


# Add into your crontab

# badip
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.torexit')
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.torrelay')
30 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badip.global')
32 * * * * run_cmd('load/badip')

# baddx, badspotter, badnode, badword
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN -O baddx.run https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/baddx')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN -O badspotter.run https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badspotter')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN -O badnode.run https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badnode')
33 * * * * spawn('cd /spider/local_data; wget -qN -O badword.new.run https://github.com/EA3CV/dxspider_info/blob/main/download/badword.new')
#35 * * * * run_cmd('load/badwords')
